The Goldschmidt tolerance factor t is calculated according to Eq. (1) using the ionic radii of the involved A, B, and X ions (rA, rB, and rX) [41, 43, 44]. It can be used to evaluate which mismatches in size of the A, B, and X ions are tolerated to form perovskite-like structures:1μ=rBrXt=(rA+rX)2rB+rX.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
